The Chronicle Harare Bureau President Mnangagwa has sworn-in Justice Loice Matanda-Moyo as the new chairperson of the Zimbabwe Anti-Corruption (ZACC) Commission at a brief ceremony held at State House today. <img class="wp-image-451749 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/05/Matanda.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="373" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/05/Matanda.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/05/Matanda-360x197.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> President Mnangagwa Thursday morning presided over the swearing-in ceremony of Justice Loice Matanda-Moyo as the new chairperson of the Zimbabwe Anti-Corruption Commission. Justice Matanda-Moyo is expected to give fresh impetus to the nation’s drive to eradicate the scourge that has assumed epidemic proportions across the country’s economic sectors. More to follow…